{"article_id":"SZGLHMy49pfn8F8w","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Iowa Democratic Party hasn ' t announced the results of even a single precinct from Monday night ' s Iowa caucuses ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"leading longtime political observers to declare the event a debacle .","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"The state party said Tuesday morning","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"it expects results later in the day .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"In explaining what went wrong ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"the party cited \" coding \" problems with a new app","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"used to collect the results","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"and hinted at the complexity of this year ' s process .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"\" It became clear that there were inconsistencies with the reports , \"","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"the party said in a statement .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"\" The underlying cause of the inconsistencies was not immediately clear ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"and required investigation ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"which took time . \"","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"This year , for the first time , the Iowa Democratic Party had planned to report how many votes each candidate earned statewide and in each precinct , as well as the number of delegates awarded .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"But it went badly .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Instead of ending in a single victory speech ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"the night wrapped up","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"with each candidate","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"giving their supporters an upbeat address","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"hinting at a win .","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"Former South Bend , Indiana , Mayor Pete Buttigieg even explicitly claimed victory .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Here ' s what we know about the delay , what ' s behind it , and when we might finally find out who won .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"The results are delayed due to \" inconsistencies \" in the reports to the state party","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"that showed up during a \" quality check \" on Monday night ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"the state party said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Results will be released \" as soon as possible \" on Tuesday ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"but are still being tallied .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"This year , precinct chairs were using a new app","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"to report their results to state party headquarters","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"- but the app \" was reporting out only partial data \" due to a \" coding issue in the reporting system , \"","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"according to the party ' s statement .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"In several statements","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"beginning Monday night ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"the Iowa Democratic Party emphasized","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"that the app was not hacked","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"and votes have not been tampered with .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"And there is a paper trail","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"because of the \" preference cards \"","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that voters filled out this year .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Bloomberg reported on Monday","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"that precinct captains were \" struggling to use the new phone application , \"","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"with four county chairs telling reporters","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"\"","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"that they were unable to download or log in to the phone app . \"","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"Some precincts abandoned the app","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"and used paper instead ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"according to Politico reporter Elena Schneider .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"The state party said in its statement","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that there were backup systems in place","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"and that results were being entered manually ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"although it was taking longer","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"than expected .","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"It ' s not clear how well the backup systems worked .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"One precinct chair tweeted Monday night","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"that he ' d tried to call in","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"to report results","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"and was on hold for an hour .","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"NBC quoted an anonymous source in the state","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"who called the phone line \" a disaster. \"","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"And Corasaniti reported","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"that the Polk County executive director ' s photographs of paper results were not accepted by the Iowa Democratic Party headquarters .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"The Sanders and Buttigieg campaigns released preliminary results","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"that suggested","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"their candidates did well ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"but official results are still being tabulated .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Buttigieg took an explicit victory lap on Monday night ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"despite the information vacuum .","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"Each candidate gave a quasi-victory speech ,","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"starting with Sen. Amy Klobuchar ,","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"rather than wait around all night .","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"The Iowa caucuses this year are a complicated process","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"involving three different vote counts .","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"For the first time , the state Democratic Party is supposed to be publicly reporting two different raw vote totals for every candidate","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"( one with all candidates in the mix and one after those","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"who did not get at least 15 percent of the vote","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"were eliminated )","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"as well as the number of delegates","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"each candidate actually wins in the final vote total .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"Some were worrying about chaos at the caucuses","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"even before voting began ,","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"and by Monday afternoon , reports were trickling out about problems with the mobile app","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"that precinct chairs were supposed to be using","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"to report their results .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"Iowa is not a particularly delegate-rich state ;","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"its significance comes from its first-in-the-nation status ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"which gives it an ability","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"to reshape expectations among the media , donors , and political partisans .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"Winning Iowa doesn ' t put you on track , on its own , to amassing an unbeatable number of delegates .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"It just feeds a narrative ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"and","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"when it comes to Iowa ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"perception really is reality .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Under those circumstances , the later the results","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"- and the more the conversation focuses on the process -","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"the less time the winner has to capitalize .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"This is probably right","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"https : //t.co/n7NS7RUwPi","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"- Nate Silver","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"( @ NateSilver538 )","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"February 4 , 2020","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"But more broadly , the delay also appeared to be undermining the legitimacy of the caucus process","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"- including both high-profile critiques of Iowa ' s first-in-the-nation status and conspiracy theories","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that the party was somehow rigging the election .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"The Iowa caucuses have long been a target of criticism","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"for being too unrepresentative of the country and too inaccessible .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Now critics and skeptics have another charge","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"to add to the pile :","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"the caucuses were a mess .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"As early as 8:48 pm Eastern time , the New York Times was already reporting","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"that problems with the app were giving rise to conspiracy theories .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"\" One of the risks","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"of introducing apps like this , and new technology more generally , into elections ,","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"is that problems occur ,","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"as they inevitably do , \"","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Matt Blaze , a professor of computer science and law at Georgetown University , told the Times .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"\" People might see this as evidence","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"that the whole system is rigged . \"","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"This view got worse","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"as the night went on .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"A viral tweet suggested ,","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"without evidence ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"that the app was being used","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"to somehow rig the process against Bernie Sanders .","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"Many of Sanders ' s supporters bear a grudge against the party from the 2016 primary ,","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"and in the absence of a clear explanation for what ' s happening ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"it ' s likely conspiracy theories like these will continue to spread .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"Meanwhile , President Trump ' s campaign manager Brad Pascale , seized on the delay","depth":4},{"id":127,"text":"to suggest","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"that the Democratic Party is rigging things somehow :","depth":5},{"id":129,"text":"Quality control = rigged ?","depth":4},{"id":130,"text":"https : //t.co/rJY3gdRccE","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"- Brad Parscale -","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"Text TRUMP to 88022","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"( @ parscale )","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"February 4 , 2020","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"The Trump campaign has good reason","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"to want to see Democrats divided","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"going into the general election ,","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"even if there ' s no evidence , so far , of any malice rather than technical difficulties .","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"But in an emotional and heated election , against the backdrop of a process","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"that many Sanders fans thought","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"was unfair in 2016","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"and a president","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"who constantly accuses his opponents of cheating ,","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"it ' s important that the US electoral system seems functional .","depth":5},{"id":145,"text":"The Iowa delay seems to be , so far , a step in the wrong direction .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":291,"left":271,"right":290,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":271,"left":215,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":206,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":158,"right":205,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":149,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":147,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":152,"right":156,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":4,"right":151,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":7,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":15